NOTICE — third-party provenance for data/skill-index.json
==========================================================

This project (MIT-licensed) ships a metadata INDEX of publicly-listed Claude Code
skills and plugins in `data/skill-index.json`, generated by
`scripts/refresh-skill-index.mjs` (`npm run refresh-index`).

WHAT THE INDEX CONTAINS
-----------------------
For each listed skill/plugin the index stores FACTS: the skill/plugin name, its
source URL, its install command, its upstream repository star count and pinned
commit SHA, and — only where the source license permits — a short description.
Names, URLs, and install commands are facts about publicly-published software and
are not themselves creative works subject to copyright.

LICENSE-AWARE DESCRIPTIONS
--------------------------
Descriptions are the one field that can carry an upstream author's copyrighted
prose. The generator classifies each source's license and ships a description
VERBATIM only when the source is positively permissively licensed. Where the
source is NOT permissively licensed (or its license cannot be positively
determined), the verbatim description is EXCLUDED and replaced with a short,
factual, name-derived phrase.

SOURCES AND THEIR LICENSES (verified 2026-07-02)
------------------------------------------------
1. anthropics/skills — MIXED, per-skill licensing (no repo-level LICENSE file).
   Each skill carries its own `skills/<name>/LICENSE.txt` and a SKILL.md
   frontmatter `license:` field.
     - Apache-2.0 skills (frontmatter "Complete terms in LICENSE.txt"):
       algorithmic-art, brand-guidelines, canvas-design, claude-api,
       frontend-design, internal-comms, mcp-builder,
       slack-gif-creator, theme-factory, web-artifacts-builder, webapp-testing
       → descriptions SHIPPED VERBATIM (Apache-2.0 permits redistribution).
     - Proprietary / all-rights-reserved skills (frontmatter
       "Proprietary. LICENSE.txt has complete terms";
       "© 2025 Anthropic, PBC. All rights reserved."):
       docx, pdf, pptx, xlsx
       → descriptions EXCLUDED, replaced with a name-derived phrase.
     - License not machine-confirmable at scrape time (treated as unknown →
       descriptions EXCLUDED, name-derived phrase): doc-coauthoring, skill-creator
       → treated as unknown → description EXCLUDED (fail-safe).

2. anthropics/claude-plugins-official — repo-level Apache-2.0
   → plugin descriptions SHIPPED VERBATIM (permissive).

3. jeremylongshore/claude-code-plugins-plus-skills — repo-level MIT (community,
   trust:"community", subject to an additional injection lint before inclusion)
   → curated descriptions SHIPPED VERBATIM (permissive).

Each index entry records a `licenseClass` ("permissive" | "restricted" |
"unknown") so this decision is auditable per-entry.

